-- Rakuten, Baidu Open China Internet Mall Venture, Wall Street Journal Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-18T19:48:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/rakuten-baidu-open-china-internet-mall-venture-wall-street-journal-says.html
Rakuten Inc. opened an online
shopping center in China with Baidu Inc., with plans to invest
$50 million over three years, the Wall Street Journal said,
citing Rakuten Chief Executive Officer Hiroshi Mikitani.  The venture has about 2,000 registered merchants, the
newspaper said. Mikitani spoke at a news conference in Tokyo,
the WSJ said. Rakuten announced plans for the venture in
January.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  